reviews.title: Direct Marketing to your children!  AVOID
reviews.comment: DON\'T BOTHER The app has on the top of the list a number of pay-for apps which cannot be removed from the screen.  They ask for your child\'s age to directly market these apps to your child.  Unless you have a large screen, these pay-for apps will take up half your screen.  Even if you buy these apps, only more pay-for apps will appear.    HEADACHES from constantly being asked to purchased these apps from my kids when there are numerous free apps available. reviews.title: Best headache prevention ever
reviews.comment: Whether my toddler is getting fussy on long car rides or at extended waits at the doctor\'s office, this app helps prevent me from getting a headache by allowing her to play with my tablet without me worrying about her messing anything up. I did have a minor glitch for a while where she was able to get around the kid lock, but that\'s now resolved, and the app is working perfectly. Famigo was very quick and helpful while working with me to resolve the issue. Recommended!

reviews.title: Love It!
reviews.comment: I have this app for my tablet and love it! It keeps my device safe from my 3 year old son and my 1.5 year old twins. LOVE that I can monitor how much they are playing each week too :) My one suggestion: allows multiple users - I\'d love to be able to sign in each kid for tracking and for different active apps!
